    {
      "id": "ml89h5qf",
      "questionNumber": 2,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "section": "A",
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "questionText": "<p>An organic compound $(\\mathrm{P})$ on treatment with aqueous ammonia under hot condition forms compound $(\\mathrm{Q})$ which on heating with $\\mathrm{Br}_2$ and KOH forms compound $(\\mathrm{R})$ having molecular formula $\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_7 \\mathrm{~N}$. Names of P, Q and R respectively are.</p>\n",
      "options": [
        "<p>Toluic acid, methylbenzamide, 2-methylaniline</p>\n",
        "<p>Benzoic acid, benzamide, aniline</p>\n",
        "<p>Benzoic acid, 4-methylbenzamide, 4-methylaniline</p>\n",
        "<p>Phenylethanoic acid, phenylethanamide, benzamine</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 1,
      "solution": "<p>$$ \\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_7 \\mathrm{N} \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{DU}=4 $$</p>\n<p>DU (Degree of Unsaturation) equal to 4 tells us there is one benzene ring in the molecule.</p>\n<p>With the formula $\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_7 \\mathrm{~N}$ and one benzene ring, the compound must be aniline, which is a benzene ring attached to an $\\mathrm{NH_2}$ group.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mlv8d1p1/b754c640-ccbc-4a15-b614-3e03779541d7/f28c9050-0e8a-11f1-b022-01661775bb49/file-6y3zli1mlv8d1p2.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mlv8d1p1/b754c640-ccbc-4a15-b614-3e03779541d7/f28c9050-0e8a-11f1-b022-01661775bb49/file-6y3zli1mlv8d1p2.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 21st January Morning Shift Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 20 English Explanation\"></p>",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "topic": "Compounds Containing Nitrogen"
    },
