      "id": "mnswhq98",
      "questionNumber": 11,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "section": "A",
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "questionText": "<p>Arrange the following compounds according to increasing order of boiling points.</p>\n<p>$$ \\mathrm{n}-\\mathrm{C}_4 \\mathrm{H}_9 \\mathrm{OH}(\\mathrm{~A}), \\mathrm{n}-\\mathrm{C}_4 \\mathrm{H}_9 \\mathrm{NH}_2(\\mathrm{~B}), \\mathrm{n}-\\mathrm{C}_4 \\mathrm{H}_{10}(\\mathrm{C}) \\text { and } \\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{NHC}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5(\\mathrm{D}) . $$</p>",
      "options": [
        "<p>$$ \\mathrm{C}<\\mathrm{B}<\\mathrm{A}<\\mathrm{D} $$</p>",
        "<p>$$ \\mathrm{D}<\\mathrm{C}<\\mathrm{B}<\\mathrm{A} $$</p>",
        "<p>$$ \\mathrm{C}<\\mathrm{D}<\\mathrm{B}<\\mathrm{A} $$</p>",
        "<p>$$ \\mathrm{D}<\\mathrm{B}<\\mathrm{A}<\\mathrm{C} $$</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "solution": "<p>(A) $n-\\mathrm{C_4H_9OH}$ (an alcohol) forms strong intermolecular hydrogen bonding between $\\mathrm{O-H}$ groups of different molecules. Because of this strong attraction, more heat is needed to separate the molecules, so its boiling point is the highest.</p>\n<p>(B) $n-\\mathrm{C_4H_9NH_2}$ (a primary amine) also shows intermolecular hydrogen bonding due to the presence of $\\mathrm{N-H}$ bonds. But nitrogen is less electronegative than oxygen, so $\\mathrm{N-H}$ hydrogen bonding is weaker than $\\mathrm{O-H}$ hydrogen bonding. Hence, its boiling point is lower than the alcohol.</p>\n<p>(C) $n-\\mathrm{C_4H_{10}}$ is a non-polar hydrocarbon. It cannot form hydrogen bonds. Only weak van der Waals (London dispersion) forces act between its molecules, so it has the lowest boiling point.</p>\n<p>(D) $\\mathrm{C_2H_5NHC_2H_5}$ (a secondary amine) can form hydrogen bonding, but it is weaker than in $n-\\mathrm{C_4H_9NH_2}$ because it has only one $\\mathrm{N-H}$ bond (fewer chances for hydrogen bonding). So its boiling point is lower than (B), but higher than the hydrocarbon (C).</p>\n<p>Therefore, the increasing order of boiling points is:</p>\n<p>$$C < D < B < A$$</p>",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "topic": "Compounds Containing Nitrogen"
    },
